1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,740
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,740 --> 00:00:03,480
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:09,580
Sir, I believe
you have the wrong person.

5
00:00:10,180 --> 00:00:14,420
I'm not Kim Dan Hui.
My name is Kim Myung Hui.

6
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:15,920
Right.

7
00:00:17,020 --> 00:00:18,690
I thought
something was off at first, too.

8
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,030
You must've changed your name.

9
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:24,100
I'm Kim Myung Hui, sir.

10
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:28,100
I see.
You're going to play dumb, are you?

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:33,240
What, do I have to bring you a copy
of your family records?

12
00:00:33,810 --> 00:00:35,340
By all means, bring them.

13
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:39,310
I'll get my official registration
to prove I'm Kim Myung Hui.

14
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:43,680
If your proof is conclusive,

15
00:00:44,050 --> 00:00:47,390
you'll get the money
you think you're owed.

16
00:00:49,350 --> 00:00:50,360
Proof?

17
00:00:52,390 --> 00:00:53,460
That's rich.

18
00:00:55,590 --> 00:00:56,830
I'm the proof.

19
00:00:57,430 --> 00:00:59,160
My memory is the proof.

20
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:00,570
If you make accusations...

21
00:01:01,070 --> 00:01:04,040
and demand money without proof,

22
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:06,100
I'll have...

23
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:09,210
no choice but to take legal action.

24
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,080
Legal action?

25
00:01:13,210 --> 00:01:14,210
Legal action?

26
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:20,150
You wait right here.

27
00:01:21,050 --> 00:01:23,820
I'll be back
with that "proof" you like so much,

28
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:26,060
so just wait.

29
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,900
He really is the nephew
of your adoptive parents, isn't he?

30
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:36,870
Yes.

31
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:38,540
Can you really afford
to just let him go like that?

32
00:01:40,210 --> 00:01:41,440
If I show any weakness,

33
00:01:41,970 --> 00:01:44,340
he'll latch on and won't let go.

34
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:49,280
First, I need to see
what cards he's holding.

35
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,280
That's true.

36
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,790
Officially, Kim Dan Hui is dead,

37
00:01:54,790 --> 00:01:57,160
and you've been Kim Myung Hui
for the last 30 years.

38
00:01:57,860 --> 00:02:00,890
So unless he brings solid proof,
we have the upper hand.

39
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,940
Darn it.

40
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:16,570
I talked a big game,
and now she wants proof?

41
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:20,810
After my uncle died,
all his stuff was likely thrown out.

42
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,050
Seriously.

43
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,050
She's not Kim Myung Hui.
She's Kim Dan Hui.

44
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:28,650
How do I prove it?

45
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:31,820
Hold on.

46
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:41,430
What did you just say?

47
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,040
She's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui?

48
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:11,630
Seriously. Stop stuffing your face
and talk to me.

49
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:13,870
I clearly heard you say...

50
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:16,700
she's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui.

51
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,900
What's that supposed to mean?

52
00:03:20,940 --> 00:03:21,940
Darn.

53
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:25,980
What did I mean by that?

54
00:03:35,890 --> 00:03:36,890
Money.

55
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:38,490
- Money?
- Money?

56
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,390
Yes, pay up first.

57
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:48,000
You're clearly dying to know,
and I can't just tell you for free.

58
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:50,100
For free? Give me a break.

59
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,000
You just ate two whole bowls
on my dime.

60
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,320
If you're really that curious,

61
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:07,850
have a large bill ready...

62
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,560
and give me a call at this number.

63
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:18,400
On second thought, half will do.

64
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,370
I'll even do it for half,
so just give me a call.

65
00:04:23,570 --> 00:04:24,570
Later.

66
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,410
He's so obviously a con artist.

67
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:38,520
Don't fall for his act
when he's just all talk.

68
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,620
What do you mean he has nothing?

69
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:43,490
He gave us the name.

70
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,790
Kim Dan Hui, not Kim Myung Hui.

71
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:51,060
I know there's something to this.

72
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:58,440
All he knows is my name.

73
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,470
Even if he is
my adoptive father's nephew,

74
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:02,770
he doesn't know I had a twin.

75
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:06,440
Right. If he knew, he wouldn't
have mentioned changing your name.

76
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,180
He doesn't even know
that Kim Dan Hui is dead.

77
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:10,880
That's lucky for us.

78
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:15,020
And he seemed to squirm
when I mentioned legal action.

79
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,020
That, and the fact
that he's asking for money.

80
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:19,290
Look into him for me.

81
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:22,730
Okay, got it.
I already spoke with Woo Jin.

82
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:27,370
Assemblyman Kwon.

83
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,940
Isn't our deadline coming up?

84
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:34,410
It is, but why are you
suddenly bringing him up?

85
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:38,140
Set up a meeting for me.
I need to finalize our deal.

86
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:39,940
Right now, with everything going on?

87
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:43,310
Shouldn't we focus on solving
this other problem first?

88
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:47,220
This might actually help us
solve our problem.

89
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:57,460
This is one of the personal effects
from the car explosion?

90
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:01,070
Yes, but it's been seven years
since the explosion.

91
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:02,770
Would there be any prints left?

92
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:07,670
When fingerprint residue oxidizes
or carbonizes under high heat,

93
00:06:07,770 --> 00:06:10,070
it leaves a chemical trace
on the surface.

94
00:06:11,410 --> 00:06:15,380
Latent prints are sometimes detected
on metal or glass surfaces.

95
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:19,420
Those are the exact kinds of samples
my research team looks for.

96
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:22,050
Are you saying there's a chance?

97
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:26,720
Every item is different,
so I can't make any promises.

98
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:27,790
But...

99
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:31,060
if even a partial trace remains,

100
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:35,570
we can use advanced forensic methods
like vacuum metal deposition...

101
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:38,270
to develop even old latent prints.

102
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,670
I see.

103
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:43,140
Could you give it a shot then?

104
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:48,410
This is a reference fingerprint.

105
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:52,080
If you are able to restore a print,
please run a comparison.

106
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:57,360
Understood. I'll do my best.

107
00:07:12,770 --> 00:07:13,770
What is it?

108
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:17,280
Chloe had to report her proposal
to Producer Shin.

109
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:20,280
I thought it'd be better
coming from me than from her.

110
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:27,150
You can leave now.

111
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,390
I have a guest.

112
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:50,840
Is there someone
Min Jun's meeting for work...

113
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,510
that I don't know about?

114
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:56,810
If this isn't about work,

115
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,250
then what is it about?

116
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:07,930
You must be Director Kim.

117
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:12,260
I should've greeted you earlier
when you were with Director Park.

118
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:15,230
I blanked for a moment
and didn't recognize you.

119
00:08:15,530 --> 00:08:16,530
I'm sorry about that.

120
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:20,540
No, I think
you have the wrong person.

121
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:23,370
Oh, my. Aren't you Director Kim?

122
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:27,510
But you look so familiar.
Who are you again?

123
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:31,880
I'm a forensic science professor
at Hanguk University.

124
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,450
I haven't worked
with Adele Group before,

125
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,150
so we probably haven't met.

126
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:38,660
Oh, right. I'm sorry about that.

127
00:08:39,090 --> 00:08:43,430
So what brings
a forensic science professor here?

128
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:46,030
I'm here as a technical consultant.

129
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,630
As for the details,

130
00:08:48,470 --> 00:08:51,470
you should discuss them
with Director Park Min Jun.

131
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,540
What were you grilling
the professor about?

132
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:04,620
I wonder what technical advice
we'd need from a forensics expert.

133
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:08,120
I'm strengthening internal security
and upgrading our systems.

134
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,220
To prepare for any potential leaks,

135
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:13,220
we need a system
that can secure evidence.

136
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,330
That's why I brought him in
as a consultant.

137
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:18,130
- Any other questions?
- No, I'm good.

138
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:37,550
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

139
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:49,090
If I tell Chloe I'm comparing
her prints to Jin Ju's,

140
00:09:49,430 --> 00:09:51,230
she'll be offended for sure.

141
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:56,830
This could be all for nothing,
so it's better not to tell her.

142
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:05,740
What do you think?

143
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:08,150
Isn't it an exact match
for the original design?

144
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,250
Yes.

145
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:14,250
It's instantly recognizable.

146
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,320
What's wrong?

147
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:21,090
Is this bringing up bad memories?

148
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:28,830
No.

149
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:32,270
It's just a watch.

150
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:36,310
A tool to get under
Choi Yu Na's skin.

151
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:39,080
The card I'll use to trap her.

152
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:58,260
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

153
00:11:11,810 --> 00:11:12,810
Yes, Dad.

154
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:15,910
I got the watch you sent.

155
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:18,320
It turned out just like the design.

156
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,720
Yes, thank you.

157
00:11:24,090 --> 00:11:25,160
This watch...

158
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:27,090
What is this?

159
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:29,160
I told you...

160
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:33,500
that I was preparing
a winning move for you.

161
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:36,530
This watch...

162
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:38,970
is your ace in the hole?

163
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:41,240
I had my dad look into it.

164
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,010
Producer Shin is a watch collector,

165
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:46,040
and he prefers rare pieces
over luxury brands.

166
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:51,120
So I had a custom watch made
as a gift.

167
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,990
This watch...

168
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:57,460
Where did you get the design for it?

169
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:02,290
Of course. I knew
you'd recognize your own design.

170
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:04,500
Seven years ago,

171
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:07,530
you won the grand prize
in a design competition...

172
00:12:08,430 --> 00:12:09,830
for a his-and-hers watch.

173
00:12:11,070 --> 00:12:12,070
What?

174
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:15,410
You figured out he had a girlfriend,

175
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:18,940
so the his-and-hers watch
you designed yourself...

176
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:21,780
seemed like
the perfect heartfelt gift.

177
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:26,350
It's a one-of-a-kind,
award-winning matching set.

178
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:29,420
I'm sure Producer Shin will love it.

179
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:33,620
Here you go.

180
00:12:34,290 --> 00:12:38,660
Go ahead,
win Mr. Shin's heart with this gift.

181
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:51,340
If you don't want to,
I'll give it to him myself.

182
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:52,710
No.

183
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:02,420
It's a gift based on my design,
so I'll give it to him myself.

184
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:05,060
And I'll be the one...

185
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:07,490
to win his heart.

186
00:13:08,690 --> 00:13:09,690
Good.

187
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,460
I have a meeting
with Producer Shin tomorrow,

188
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,430
so get there before I do
and give it to him.

189
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:31,680
Just as I thought.
That's Choi Yu Na for you.

190
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:45,160
That watch? No,

191
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:49,000
your past is going
to ruin this deal.

192
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:02,380
What are you hiding?

193
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,580
What do you mean?

194
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,250
I've got an appointment to get to.

195
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:26,400
I have a meeting
with Producer Shin tomorrow.

196
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:29,470
Could you be there?

197
00:14:31,110 --> 00:14:33,910
Are you asking me for help?

198
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:37,180
I'm asking you to attend
as the head of the bio division.

199
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:40,750
As the one who can vouch
for the contents of the proposal.

200
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:44,560
But if that makes you uncomfortable,
so be it.

201
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,140
She's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui.

202
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:06,940
People wouldn't come looking for her
just because she changed her name.

203
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:09,750
What on earth is she hiding?

204
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,020
Goodness.

205
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:15,050
What are you doing here
when the owner isn't around?

206
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:17,690
I'm looking for something.
Mind your own business.

207
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,290
I'm afraid I can't do that.

208
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:24,960
The chairman ordered extra vigilance
after Ms. Choi broke into his study.

209
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,060
Are you comparing me to Ms. Choi?

210
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,670
You're snooping just like her,
aren't you?

211
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:31,040
Why you little...

212
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,970
What are you doing?

213
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:37,510
There you go again.

214
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:40,340
You can't just go around
hitting people.

215
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:42,610
Before I report this
to the chairman,

216
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:45,980
put your arm down and get out. Now.

217
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:50,150
Are you crazy? Hey, let go of me!

218
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:53,320
- Leave the room.
- I said, let go!

219
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:56,530
Let go of me!
Have you lost your mind?

220
00:15:56,890 --> 00:16:00,860
Hey! What's all this noise?

221
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:05,040
Honey. Sir. Mrs. Ok, she...

222
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:10,070
What's that?

223
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:12,340
The chairman gave them to me.

224
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:17,450
What about me? I love flowers too.

225
00:16:17,450 --> 00:16:19,520
Please. Don't be ridiculous.

226
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:24,250
While you were with Ms. Choi
making a scene,

227
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:29,430
Myung Hui closed the deal
with Assemblyman Kwon.

228
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,760
What...

229
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,100
She closed the deal?

230
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:34,530
That's right.

231
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:37,000
She met with Assemblyman Kwon
and finalized it today.

232
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:40,140
She earned every bit of it,

233
00:16:40,570 --> 00:16:43,810
so stop trying to pick a fight.
Good grief.

234
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:56,150
The flowers are so beautiful.

235
00:16:56,250 --> 00:17:00,720
Here, let me take them.
I'll arrange them on the table.

236
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:02,860
Thank you.

237
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:04,500
You're welcome.

238
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,560
Hello?

239
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:39,730
This is the wife
of the Adele Group's chairman.

240
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:43,070
Look. I'll pay you for dirt
on Kim Myung Hui.

241
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:44,640
Stop that.

242
00:17:44,870 --> 00:17:46,570
What do you think you're doing?

243
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,310
What do you mean you'll pay him?

244
00:17:49,740 --> 00:17:52,780
I'm telling you,
he's a con man who knows nothing.

245
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:55,080
If he's got nothing,
we'll make something up.

246
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,310
What?

247
00:17:57,450 --> 00:18:00,280
He claims she's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui,

248
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,790
so we'll work with that.

249
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:05,520
"Kim Myung Hui faked her ID
and is hiding a secret."

250
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:07,520
We have to use that against her...

251
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,330
before Tae Ho's heart
is completely hers.

252
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,400
Yes, it's me.

253
00:18:21,910 --> 00:18:23,010
You did great.

254
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:28,380
Now that we've closed the deal
with Assemblyman Kwon,

255
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:31,350
we need to prepare
the lobbying funds.

256
00:18:31,450 --> 00:18:33,180
So here's what I'm saying.

257
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:38,620
Myung Hui, I want you
to take charge of the gallery and...

258
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:40,120
No way.

259
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:44,290
You can't put that witch in charge.

260
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:57,570
Kim Myung Hui, no, Kim Dan Hui.

261
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:01,080
She's been tricking all of us.

262
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:05,750
Not this again.

263
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:08,620
What kind of stunt
are you pulling now?

264
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:13,220
What nonsense are you spewing
with a man who's been complaining...

265
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:16,360
about Myung Hui's jewelry appraisal
backing you up?

266
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:18,400
Jewelry appraisal, my foot.

267
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:21,170
This person is here to testify
that Kim Myung Hui,

268
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:25,500
or rather, that fraud,
has falsified her identity.

269
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:29,710
He's the witness
who will expose her secret.

270
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,440
What?

271
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,280
Hold on.

272
00:19:33,710 --> 00:19:35,810
What are you talking about?

273
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:41,250
Myung Hui, answer me.
What is this all about?

274
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,830
Have you had a chance
to look over the proposal?

275
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:51,060
I have.

276
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:54,130
You've shown clearly how it fits
the concept for my documentary.

277
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:58,040
In that case, have you considered
proceeding with a contract?

278
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:01,910
Let me be frank.

279
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:09,550
What's this?

280
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,080
It's from Ms. Choi Yu Na.

281
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:14,520
It's a gift.

282
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:16,220
Or rather,

283
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:18,790
a bribe.

284
00:20:19,490 --> 00:20:22,230
A background check, threats,
and now a bribe.

285
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,930
She's not the kind of person
I want to work with.

286
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:26,930
However...

287
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:35,910
Her offer to fund the production
is hard to ignore.

288
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:38,480
(Brand Partnership Proposal)

289
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,050
Is that so?

290
00:20:43,850 --> 00:20:45,220
What about you, Chloe?

291
00:20:46,820 --> 00:20:51,390
Can you match this level
of financial support?

292
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:58,760
That would be difficult.

293
00:21:08,710 --> 00:21:11,170
I'm Park Min Jun,
a director at Adele Group.

294
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:14,240
A pleasure to meet you.

295
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:21,890
Chloe asked me
to attend this meeting.

296
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:25,060
I believe she wanted me to explain
our position on production funding.

297
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:28,390
May I join you for a moment?

298
00:21:29,060 --> 00:21:30,060
Please, have a seat.

299
00:21:40,670 --> 00:21:41,670
This...

300
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:44,040
What is this?

301
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,910
Apparently, Ms. Choi
gave Producer Shin a gift.

302
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:52,680
A gift?

303
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:56,990
She tried to bribe me,
knowing I like watches.

304
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,170
Using a design she stole,

305
00:22:08,170 --> 00:22:10,030
she's now trying to bribe her way
into the contract.

306
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,310
A stolen design?

307
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:19,740
Ms. Choi Yu Na stole
someone else's design.

308
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:25,020
I can't believe she had the nerve
to pull a stunt like this.

309
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,690
And calling this a gift?
Unbelievable.

310
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:34,790
I'm sure the funding
Ms. Choi promised is impressive,

311
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:38,130
but once the contract is signed
and circumstances change,

312
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:40,900
there's no telling
how she'll behave.

313
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,770
She uses people's weaknesses
against them...

314
00:22:43,770 --> 00:22:45,800
and gives gifts made
from stolen designs.

315
00:22:48,470 --> 00:22:50,070
Can you really trust
someone like that?

316
00:22:58,820 --> 00:23:00,920
We'll be in touch, Mr. Shin.

317
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:04,250
I'll contact you soon.
Until next time, Director Park.

318
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,320
Sure.

319
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:16,570
Why did you really call me here?

320
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:20,470
Like I said,
it was about the production budget.

321
00:23:20,470 --> 00:23:21,470
No.

322
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:22,940
You, of all people,

323
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:24,910
could've explained that perfectly
on your own.

324
00:23:26,310 --> 00:23:29,980
The reason it had to be me,
that watch from Choi Yu Na...

325
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:36,850
You needed someone to call it
a stolen design, didn't you?

326
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:41,420
Am I wrong? Be honest with me.

327
00:23:48,530 --> 00:23:52,570
I told you to tell me
what's going on.

328
00:23:57,270 --> 00:24:00,640
Actually, there's something
I'd like to ask you, sir.

329
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:04,410
Do you believe I'm Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui...

330
00:24:04,710 --> 00:24:06,080
like they say?

331
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:14,390
Are you saying I'm not
who I say I am?

332
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:18,530
That's right.
You have adoptive parents,

333
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,300
but you cut them off...

334
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,000
and pretended to be an orphan...

335
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,100
to gain the chairman's sympathy
and get close to him.

336
00:24:24,370 --> 00:24:27,600
Do you have any proof
to back that up?

337
00:24:29,370 --> 00:24:30,370
Right here.

338
00:24:31,540 --> 00:24:33,510
The person who knows you
as Kim Dan Hui.

339
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,280
Your adoptive parents' nephew
is our witness.

340
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:42,220
Can you really call a con artist
who's wanted by the police...

341
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,590
a solid witness?

342
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:49,090
What? He's wanted by the police?

343
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,400
You're a con artist,
just as I thought.

344
00:25:03,810 --> 00:25:06,640
She's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui?

345
00:25:10,710 --> 00:25:13,620
Can we talk for a minute?

346
00:25:14,150 --> 00:25:15,650
But I'm kind of busy.

347
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,450
Come on. This way.

348
00:25:34,170 --> 00:25:35,910
He's so obviously a con artist.

349
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:39,980
Don't fall for his act
when he's just all talk.

350
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:43,080
What do you mean he has nothing?

351
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:44,980
He gave us the name.

352
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:47,280
Kim Dan Hui, not Kim Myung Hui.

353
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:53,390
I know there's something to this.

354
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:05,600
So, what was Oh Jung Ran's reaction?

355
00:26:06,340 --> 00:26:08,140
I didn't follow her after that,

356
00:26:08,510 --> 00:26:09,870
but it looks like
she's going to pay him.

357
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:16,410
(Wanted, Bukbu Police Station)

358
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:18,920
Being a wanted con artist,
he must've really laid it on thick.

359
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:21,480
A wanted con artist?

360
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:23,520
Is that why he kept demanding money?

361
00:26:23,990 --> 00:26:26,120
The chairman's wife
doesn't pinch pennies,

362
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:29,160
and she's obsessed
with digging up dirt on Dan Hui.

363
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:33,130
She'll surely throw money at this
to see if his story checks out.

364
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:36,930
Isn't this getting too risky
for you?

365
00:26:37,130 --> 00:26:40,400
If she learns you're not Myung Hui
and that you were adopted,

366
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,110
she'll know something is up.

367
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:45,810
Should we keep them from meeting?

368
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:47,080
No.

369
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:49,450
In fact,
we should make sure they meet.

370
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:53,950
That way, anything Oh Jung Ran says
will be seen as a con artist's lies.

371
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:56,450
Wait. Is that how it works?

372
00:26:56,750 --> 00:27:00,090
But won't Chairman Park
be suspicious?

373
00:27:01,020 --> 00:27:03,790
That's why I said I'd close the deal
with Assemblyman Kwon.

374
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:08,000
Once he's blinded by the joy
of closing the deal,

375
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:11,170
he'll be more inclined to trust me
than Oh Jung Ran.

376
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:14,100
Sir.

377
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:18,780
Ms. Oh was fooled by a con artist
and is trying to frame me.

378
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:22,780
Is he really...

379
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,520
a wanted con artist?

380
00:27:28,550 --> 00:27:30,820
Go ahead, call the police
and confirm it yourself.

381
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:32,420
Fine.

382
00:27:38,090 --> 00:27:40,000
- Darn it.
- Hey!

383
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,700
That son of a...

384
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:44,700
Unbelievable.

385
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:52,910
When he claimed I was Kim Dan Hui
and demanded money,

386
00:27:53,410 --> 00:27:55,610
I knew something was off.

387
00:27:57,980 --> 00:28:01,720
I didn't expect you to fall
for such an absurd story.

388
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:05,960
Oh Jung Ran.

389
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,890
How dare you bring a con artist
into my home?

390
00:28:09,890 --> 00:28:12,100
When on earth are you going to come
to your senses?

391
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:13,460
Honey.

392
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:17,030
No, wait.
I'm sure there's more to it.

393
00:28:17,030 --> 00:28:18,200
Enough!

394
00:28:27,010 --> 00:28:30,180
I wanted you at the meeting
because...

395
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,580
Ms. Choi's proposed financing
was excessive.

396
00:28:34,150 --> 00:28:38,760
I hoped someone from Adele Group
would agree it was reckless.

397
00:28:40,660 --> 00:28:43,060
And the watch design?

398
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:47,260
How was I supposed to know
Ms. Choi stole that design?

399
00:28:49,770 --> 00:28:53,340
What exactly do you expect from me?

400
00:28:57,970 --> 00:28:58,980
By any chance,

401
00:28:59,810 --> 00:29:01,680
did the design
that Ms. Choi stole...

402
00:29:02,710 --> 00:29:06,120
belong to the woman who died?

403
00:29:07,850 --> 00:29:11,020
Do you still see me as her?

404
00:29:15,230 --> 00:29:16,360
Please...

405
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,670
Just stop.

406
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:55,900
Hello?

407
00:29:55,970 --> 00:29:58,770
This is Hanguk University's
Forensic Science Department.

408
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:04,370
We successfully lifted a fingerprint
from the watch you provided.

409
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,340
Really?

410
00:30:07,940 --> 00:30:10,210
Yes, we compared the print
from the watch...

411
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:12,080
with the sample you provided,

412
00:30:13,350 --> 00:30:14,380
and it's a match.

413
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:17,650
The two prints belong
to the same person.

414
00:31:02,630 --> 00:31:03,630
Baek Jin Ju.

415
00:31:05,970 --> 00:31:07,100
Baek Jin Ju!

416
00:32:12,670 --> 00:32:15,640
(Pearl in Red)

417
00:32:15,970 --> 00:32:20,110
I won't lose my way again.
I'll never let you go.

418
00:32:20,340 --> 00:32:21,340
Min Jun.

419
00:32:22,010 --> 00:32:23,580
I liked Min Jun first.

420
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:25,180
Jin Ju was the one
who got in the way.

421
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,820
I secured both Min Jun and Adele
through my own hard work.

422
00:32:28,990 --> 00:32:32,160
If I win this competition,
I'll finally have it all.

423
00:32:32,420 --> 00:32:34,520
You want me to find Kim Dan Hui?

424
00:32:34,620 --> 00:32:36,830
Do you still believe that con man?

425
00:32:37,090 --> 00:32:41,230
A person can lie with words,
but not with their eyes.

426
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:44,400
I'm telling you, she was very shaken
by the name Kim Dan Hui.

427
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:47,200
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
